A,B
R
A+B=\{a+b:a \in A,b \in B\}
x \in A+B \Rightarrow x=a+b,a \in A,b \in B
a\geq \inf A \text{ and } b\geq \inf(B)
x \geq \inf(A)+\inf(B) \Rightarrow\inf(A+B) \geq \inf(A)+\inf(B)
x\in A \Rightarrow x \in A+B, \text{ so we conclude that } \inf(A) \leq  \inf(A+B)
x \in B \Rightarrow x \in A+B,\text{ so we conclude that } \inf(B) \leq  \inf(A+B)
\frac{\inf(A)+\inf(B)}{2} \leq \inf(A)+\inf(B) \leq \inf(A+B)
\inf(A+B)=\inf(A)+\inf(B)
\inf (A+B)\ge \inf A+\inf B
\delta>0
a\in A, b\in B
a<\inf A+\delta
b<\inf B+\delta
a+b<\inf A+\inf B+2\delta
\inf (A+B)\le \inf A+\inf B+2\delta
\delta
x,y
a
a \leq x \leq a+\frac {y}{n}
n \geq 1
x=a
